User: My dataset has visitors, clicks, conversions, and sales (all binary variables). Besides CTR, what other KPIs can I create?
Grok:  
Yes, with a dataset of binary flags (visitors = 1/0, clicks = 1/0, conversions = 1/0, sales = 1/0), you can derive a full set of funnel KPIs beyond just CTR by simply summing each column.
Assuming you aggregate across the whole dataset (or any segment):
V = total visitors = SUM(visitors)
C = total clicks = SUM(clicks)
Conv = total conversions = SUM(conversions)
S = total sales = SUM(sales)
Besides CTR (C / V × 100), here are the most useful KPIs:
Core Funnel Rates
Overall Conversion Rate (CVR)  
CVR = (Conv / V) × 100%  
(How many visitors ultimately convert)
Micro-Conversion Rate (Click-to-Conversion Rate)  
Micro CVR = (Conv / C) × 100%  
(What % of people who clicked actually took the next step)
Sales Conversion Rate (Visitor-to-Sale)  
Sales Rate = (S / V) × 100%  
(The ultimate bottom-line metric)
Click-to-Sale Rate  
Click-to-Sale = (S / C) × 100%
Conversion-to-Sale Rate (Close Rate)  
Close Rate = (S / Conv) × 100%  
(If “conversion” = lead/add-to-cart and “sales” = purchase)
Funnel Efficiency & Drop-off Metrics
Funnel Completion Rate (Visitor → Sale)  
= (S / V) × 100% (same as #3)
Stage Drop-off Rates:
Click drop-off: 1 - (C / V)
Conversion drop-off: 1 - (Conv / C)
Sale drop-off: 1 - (S / Conv)
Bonus Derived KPIs
Average steps completed per visitor (0–3 scale): (C + Conv + S) / V
Conversion Efficiency Index (custom composite): (Conv / C) × (S / Conv) × 100
All of these are 100% calculable right now with simple SUM() / COUNT() or pivot tables in Excel, Google Sheets, SQL, Python (pandas), or any dashboard tool.
Pro tip: Calculate them both at the total level and segmented (by week, source, ad creative, landing page, etc.) — that’s where the real insights appear.
If you later add cost or revenue columns, you can instantly layer on CPA, ROAS, etc., but even with just these four binary flags you already have a complete performance funnel.
